content:
You need to add the `$INCLUDE sites-enabled/my_virtual_server` line in the "default" file located in the "/etc/freeradius/3.0/sites-enabled" directory.

This file is the main configuration file for the FreeRADIUS server. You can find the following section in the file:
```
server default {
    listen {
        ...
    }
    authorize {
    ...
    }
    authenticate {
    ...
    }
    ...
}
```
You should add the `$INCLUDE sites-enabled/my_virtual_server` line inside the "server default" block, after the "authorize" block.

So it will look something like this:
```
server default {
    listen {
        ...
    }
    authorize {
    ...
    }
    $INCLUDE sites-enabled/my_virtual_server
    authenticate {
    ...
    }
    ...
}
```
Make sure to save your changes and restart the FreeRADIUS service for the changes to take effect.
It's recommended to check the official documentation of FreeRADIUS to find out how to include virtual servers.
